<TITLE> UZ chairmen sworn in </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 23 (bdnews24.com)  Elected Upazila representatives of Dhaka and Chittagong divisions were being sworn in on Monday. Dhaka divisional commissioner Khandaker Shawkat Hossain administered the oath to 332 chairmen, vice chairmen and vice chairwomen at around 11am at the LGED auditorium in Agargaon. Of Dhaka division's 363 posts in 121 Upazila, 111 chairmen, 112 vice chairmen and 109 women vice chairmen took oath. The remaining 31 posts in different Upazila are waiting for re-elections and investigations into polls irregularities. Some 39 elected chairmen and male and female vice chairmen for 13 of Chittagong division's 14 Upazila were sworn in by divisional commissioner MA Siddique in a low-key ceremony at the port city's Circuit House. The results for Sandwip Upazila have yet to be gazetted as the chairman election must be held again, said election officials. All those being sworn in resigned from their party posts and submitted wealth statements to the local government ministry ahead of oath-taking, though some opposed the requirement. Kishoreganj Upazila chairman and Jubo League national committee member Md Ali Akbar told bdnews24.com: "I belong to a party as an individual, but I am neutral in my activities." "I left my post before taking oath. But I am not in favour of the notion. I heard the law is being amended on the matter." Deputy secretary at the LGRD ministry Habibul Kabir told bdnews24.com that swearing-in of Sylhet division Upazila representatives was completed on Sunday. Kabir said Upazila representatives of other divisions would be sworn in by March 12. bdnews24.
